anufacturer:  	Smith & Wesson
Model:  	38
Caliber:  	.38 Spl.
Barrel Length:  	2 inch
Capacity:  	5 

Here is a J-frame Snub Nose S&W model 38 Bodyguard.

Bodyguard
Next line of compact S&Ws began from S&W "Bodyguard AirWeight" model 38 revolver of 1957. This gun was a modification of a basic Chief Special revolver with the main intention to improve "carry-ability" and "draw-ablity". It was the same 5-shot, aluminium-frame, side-open cylinder revolver in .38 Spl, but it featured shrouded hammer with only a small tip of the hammer exposed. This allowed for manual cocking, which could improve accuracy, but prevented the hammer from snagging into clothes or other obstaces during the fast draw.

Good condition - small tight gap between cylinder and barrel (that's a good thing), the cylinder is solid and does not wobble. It shoots very well.

I have put maybe 60 rounds through it, although I've only owned it a few years.


Excellent weapon for conceal carry - flat hammer is unlikely to be caught on clothing, etc. Small, light and concealable. It's extremely safe (much more than a semi-auto). Perfect for a backup gun too.


I bought this weapon for $425.  without accessories at Tanner.


I have the original wood handle with diamonds for collectors that will be sent with the weapon, but also included is a crimson trace grip w/batteries and red lazer.
